Sphelo Samuel has written a letter to Speaker of Parliament Thandi Modise asking her to investigate Busisiwe Mkhwebane and her office. JOHANNESBURG - The Public Protector's representative in the Free Sate Sphelo Samuel is calling for his boss Busisiwe Mkhwebane to step down. Samuel has written a letter to Speaker of Parliament Thandi Modise asking her to investigate Mkhwebane and her office. He claims Mkhwebane is protecting some high profile politicians and is abusing her power. READ: Mkhwebane vows to fight back against removal Samuel says he will be submitting evidence to Modise. Meanwhile, the National Assembly Speaker has approved a motion to begin proceedings for removal of Mkhwebane. The motion was brought by the Democratic Alliance.